'''Asem''' is a town in [[Kumasi]] in the [[Ashanti Region]] of [[Ghana]].
<ref name=NAM>{{cite web|title=Controversy over 'Asafo Interchange' in Kumasi|url=http://www.modernghana.com/news/147256/1/controversy-over-asafo-interchange-in-kumasi.html|publisher=www.modernghana.com|accessdate=2 June 2011}}</ref>

==Town structure==
The town in under the jurisdiction of the [[Kumasi Metropolitan Assembly]] and is in the [[Subin (Ghana parliament constituency)|Subin constituency]] of the [[Ghana Parliament|Ghana parliament]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://library.fes.de/pdf-files/bueros/ghana/03610.pdf |title=Elections 2004. Ghana's Parliamentary and Presidential  Elections|accessdate=2011-06-13 |pages=11 |publisher=[[Electoral Commission of Ghana]]| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110522115353/http://library.fes.de/pdf-files/bueros/ghana/03610.pdf| archivedate= 22 May 2011 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref>

