[[File:Ministerstvo dopravy, výstavby a regionálneho rozvoja.jpg|thumb|Head office of the [[Ministry of Transport, Construction, and Regional Development]], which houses the AMIA head office]]
The '''Aviation and Maritime Investigation Authority''' ('''AMIA''',<ref name=Accinc>"[http://www.eurocontrol.int/sites/default/files/content/documents/official-documents/reports/2012-lssip2011-sk.pdf Local Single Sky Implementation (LSSIP) SLOVAKIA]." ([https://www.webcitation.org/6DUKL9yjG?url=http://www.eurocontrol.int/sites/default/files/content/documents/official-documents/reports/2012-lssip2011-sk.pdf Archive]) Government of Slovakia and [[Eurocontrol]]. Part I - Chapter 1-8 1.5.1 Technical investigations. Retrieved on 7 January 2012.</ref> {{lang-sk|'''Letecký a námorný vyšetrovací útvar'''}}, '''LNVÚ'''<ref name=Contact>"[http://www.telecom.gov.sk/index/index.php?ids=130665 Kontakt] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305062335/http://www.telecom.gov.sk/index/index.php?ids=130665 |date=2016-03-05 }}." Aviation and Maritime Investigation Authority. Retrieved on 7 January 2012. "Adresa: Ministerstvo dopravy,výstavby a regionálneho rozvoja SR Letecký a námorný vyšetrovací útvar Námestie slobody 6 P.O.BOX 100 810 05 Bratislava"</ref>) is the accident and incident investigation authority of [[Slovakia]] for aviation and nautical matters. It is an independent part of the [[Ministry of Transport, Construction, and Regional Development]].<ref name=Accinc/> Its head office is in the Ministry of Transport offices in [[Bratislava]].<ref name=Contact/><ref>"[http://www.mindop.sk/index/index.php?lang=en Home] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130128040126/http://www.mindop.sk/index/index.php?lang=en |date=2013-01-28 }}." [[Ministry of Transport, Construction, and Regional Development]]. Retrieved on 7 January 2012. "Námestie slobody č. 6 P.O.BOX 100 810 05 Bratislava Slovenská republika"</ref>

Previously, the [[Civil Aviation Inspectorate Slovak Republic]] (Štátna letecká inšpekcia SR) conducted investigations on aviation accidents and incidents.<ref>"[http://versa.bmvit.gv.at/uploads/media/19950917_Cessna_FR_182.pdf FINAL REPORT on accident investigation of the Cessna FR 182 aircraft registration OE - XXX]." ([https://www.webcitation.org/6DLESh0Dz?url=http://versa.bmvit.gv.at/uploads/media/19950917_Cessna_FR_182.pdf Archive]) Civil Aviation Inspectorate Slovak Republic. Retrieved on 7 January 2012.</ref>

