{{Infobox Union |name= 3F |country= [[Denmark]] |affiliation= [[Danish Confederation of Trade Unions|LO Denmark]] |members= 374,000 |full_name= Fagligt Fælles Forbund |native_name= KAD, SiD |image= Fagligt Fælles Forbund logo.svg |founded= 2004 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Copenhagen]], Denmark |people= [[Per Christensen_(3F)|Per Christensen]], president (Sept. 2013-) |website= http://www.3f.dk |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. --> The '''Fagligt Fælles Forbund''', usually referred to as '''3F''', is a [[trade union]] centre in [[Denmark]]. It was formed in 2004 from the merger of the Kvindeligt Arbejderforbund i Danmark, KAD (National Union of Women Workers) and the Specialarbejderforbundet i Danmark, SID (Danish General Workers' Union). KAD was founded in 1885 and was an all-women union.
The 3F is an affiliate of the [[Danish Confederation of Trade Unions]].
