{{Infobox company |name = Grafotechna |logo = |type = [[Aktiengesellschaft]] |genre = |foundation = 1951 |founder = |defunct = 1990 |location = [[Prague, Czechoslovakia]] |key_people = |industry = [[Type foundry]] |num_employees = |revenue = |homepage = }}
'''Grafotechna''' (Grafotechna n. p., Závod 5, Výroba písma, mosazných linek a matric) was a Czechoslovak type foundry, created in 1951. It ceased to exist after 1990. It was the only manufacturer of [[moveable type|metal types]] in the former [[Czechoslovakia]].
Among other things, it manufactured fonts designed by Czech type designers [[Oldřich Menhart]] and [[Josef Týfa]].
==Typefaces== These foundry types were produced by Grafotechna:<ref>Jaspert, W. Pincus, W. Turner Berry and A.F. Johnson. ''The Encyclopedia of Type Faces.'' Blandford Press Lts.: 1953, 1983, {{ISBN|0-7137-1347-X}}, p. 2408-249</ref> {{columns-list|colwidth=30em| * '''[[Brno Z]]''' (1951, [[Jan Rambousek]]) * '''[[Ceska Unciala]]''' (1945, [[Oldřich Menhart]]) * '''[[Drynkov]]''' ([[K. Drynkov]]) * '''[[Empiriana (typeface)|Empiriana]]''' (1920)<ref>Jaspert (p.83) gives the date of 1920 for this type despite the foundry only coming into existence more than twenty years later. Perhaps this is a legacy type from one of the absorbed foundries.</ref> * '''[[Figural (typeface)|Figural]]''' ([[Oldřich Menhart]]) * '''[[Garamond]]''' (1959, [[Stanislav Marso]]) * '''[[Kalab (typeface)|Kalab]]''' ([[Method Kalab]]) * '''[[Kolektiv]]''' (1952, [[S. Duda]], [[K. Misek]], [[Josef Týfa]]) * '''[[Manuscript (typeface)|Manuscript]]''' (1944-50, [[Oldřich Menhart]]) * '''[[Menhart]]''' (1938, [[Oldřich Menhart]]), originally [[Monotype Corporation|Monotype]], later Grafotechna. * '''[[Monument (typeface)|Monument]]''' (1950-52, [[Oldřich Menhart]]) * '''[[Tyfa]]''' (1959, [[Josef Týfa]]) }}
