'''The Planned Parenthood Association of Ghana''' '''(PPAG)''' is a non governmental organisation affiliated to [[International Planned Parenthood Federation]]. It was set up in 1967.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ippf.org/about-us/member-associations/ghana|title=Planned Parenthood Association of Ghana {{!}} IPPF|date=2016-03-31|work=IPPF|access-date=2018-03-31|language=en}}</ref>  A comprehensive sexuality education manual for young people titled “KnowItOwnItLiveIt” has been launched with a call on parents to intensify sex education among their children to minimise Sexually Transmitted Diseases (STDs) and teenage pregnancy in the country.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.graphic.com.gh/news/general-news/sexuality-education-materials-launched-for-the-youth.html|title=Sexuality education materials launched for the youth|last=Boateng|first=Dennis Agyei|work=Graphic Online|access-date=2018-03-31|language=en-gb}}</ref>

