{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Bondoukou |latin = Dioecesis Bondukuensis |country = {{flag|Côte d'Ivoire}} |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Bouaké|Bouaké]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |area_km2 = 40,000 |population = 680,000 |population_as_of = 2006 |catholics = 97,800 |catholics_percent= 14.4 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = Vacant }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Bondoukou''' ({{lang-la|Bondukuen(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Bondoukou]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Bouaké|Bouaké]] in [[Côte d'Ivoire]]. It was established on July 3, 1987. Its Cathedral is the [[Cathédrale Saints Odile]] in Bondoukou. Bishops of Bondoukou (Roman rite) have been [[Félix Kouadjo]] (April 22, 1996 &ndash; May 6, 2012) and [[Alexandre Kouassi]] (August 28, 1987 &ndash; December 12, 1994)
==See also== *[[Roman Catholicism in Côte d'Ivoire]] * [[List of Roman Catholic dioceses in Côte d'Ivoire]]
