{{one source|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox Union |name= |country= [[Bangladesh]] |affiliation= [[World Federation of Trade Unions|WFTU]] ,SCOPE |members= |full_name= Socialist Labours' Front (Samajtantrik Sramik Front) |native_name= সমাজতান্ত্রিক শ্রমিক ফ্রন্ট |image= |founded= |current|head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= 23/2 Topkhana road(2nd floor), [[Dhaka]], Bangladesh |people= |website=www.spb.org.bd |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''Samajtantrik Sramik Front''' is a national [[trade union]] federation in [[Bangladesh]]. It is affiliated with the [[World Federation of Trade Unions]]. Razakuzzaman Ratan is the leader of this organization.
This organization is politically tied to the [[Socialist Party of Bangladesh]]. ==References== *{{cite book | year = 2005 | title = Trade Unions of the World | editor = [[International Centre for Trade Union Rights|ICTUR]] et al., | edition = 6th | publisher = John Harper Publishing | location = London, UK | isbn = 0-9543811-5-7 }}
