'''The Fencing Master''' (French ''Le Maître d'armes'') <ref name="Alexandre2015">{{cite book|author=Dumas, Alexandre|title=Le maître d'armes: Nouvelle édition augmentée|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cfQgCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA402|date=4 December 2015|publisher=Arvensa Editions|isbn=979-10-273-0208-6|pages=402–}}</ref> is a nineteenth century novel by [[Alexandre Dumas]] <ref name="Dumas2015">{{cite book|author=Alexandre Dumas|title=The Fencing Master - Scholar's Choice Edition|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ujlNrgEACAAJ|date=14 February 2015|publisher=BiblioLife|isbn=978-1-297-00673-9}}</ref> and published in 1840-1842. The novel is set in [[Russia]].<ref name="Roberts2011">{{cite book|author=Graham H. Roberts|title=Other Voices: Three Centuries of Cultural Dialogue between Russia and Western Europe|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=vaYnBwAAQBAJ&pg=PA13&dq=The+Fencing+Master+Alexandre+Dumas&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj6nILc8MnLAhUBJ5QKHdbzBDcQ6AEIRzAJ#v=onepage&q=The%20Fencing%20Master%20Alexandre%20Dumas&f=false|date=18 January 2011|publisher=Cambridge Scholars Publishing|isbn=978-1-4438-2790-4|pages=13–}}</ref><ref name="Dumas2013">{{cite book|author=Alexandre Dumas|title=Delphi Works of Alexandre Dumas (Illustrated)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Q1UbAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT585|date=17 November 2013|publisher=Delphi Classics|isbn=978-1-908909-48-0|pages=585–}}</ref>

